               <msContents>
                  <summary>The writer requests and obtains 200 silver drachmas to cover expenses which have arisen. The reason that the money is paid is not specified in the surviving part of the letter. (TC)</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Location: Ann Arbor</note>
                     <note type="general">Pub. status: Recto; Verso is blank</note>
                     <note type="lines">1-13</note>
                     <note type="paleography">Written in a rather large cursive, and the lines move slightly upwards from left to right. (TC) The writer makes every effort to see to it that the lines reach fully to the right-hand edge of the papyrus. In some lines the final letter is extended to reach further to the edge, and in lines 4 and 8 the writer uses a space-filler. The papyrus has already been used once before; traces of a former washed out text are still visible. In line 6 the abbreviation is indicated by a short horizontal stroke above the gamma.</note>
